==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Savior
<hw>Sav"ior</hw> <pr>(s⟦amac⟧v"y⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>saveour</ets>, OF. <ets>salveor</ets>, F. <ets>sauveur</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>salvator</ets>, fr. <ets>salvare</ets> to save. See
<er>Save</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>saviour</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who saves, preserves,
or delivers from destruction or danger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically: <xex>The</xex> (or <xex>our</xex>,
<xex>your</xex>, etc.) <xex>Savior</xex>, he who brings salvation to
men; Jesus Christ, the Redeemer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Savioress</ent>⟦br⟧
